 exists today ubs represents a conglomeration of dozens of individual firms many of which date back to the th century over the years these firms merged to form the banks three major predecessors union bank of switzerland swiss bank corporation and paine webber the following is a visual illustration of the companys major mergers and acquisitions and historical predecessors although this is not necessarily a comprehensive list formed  from merger of union bank of switzerld  swiss bank corp union bank of switzerland merged in  with swiss bank corporation union bank of switzerland originally swiss banking association merged  bank in winterthur est  toggenburger bank est  aargauische kreditanstalt merged  acq  aargauische kreditanstalt est  bank in baden est  eidgenössische bank est  acq  interhandel est  acq  phillips  drew est  as ga phillips  co acq  chase investors management corporation est  as subsidiary schröder münchmeyer hengst  co merged  acq  schröder brothers  co est  münchmeyer  co est  frederick hengst  co swiss bank corporation merged in  with union bank of switzerland swiss bank corporation merged  basler  zürcher bankverein est  basler banvkerein est  as bankverein renamed in  zürcher bankverein est  basler depositenbank est  schweiz unionbank est  basler handelsbank est  acq  oconnor  associates est  acq  brinson partners est  acq  warburg dillon read merged  under sbc ownership s g warburg  co est  acq  dillon read  co est  acq  paine webber consolidated  subsidiaries in  merged in  with ubs paine webber jackson  curtis merged  paine  webber est  jackson  curtis est  mitchell hutchins est  acq  blyth eastman dillon  co merged  acq  blyth  co est  as blyth witter  co eastman dillon union securities  co merged  union securities est  as spinoff from j  w seligman  co eastman dillon  co est  kidder peabody  co est  acq  jc bradford  co est  acq  corporate governanceedit board of directorsedit the board of directors is the most senior corporate body with ul